#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:3
msgid "Consolidation"
msgstr "Konsolidering"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:5
msgid ""
"Consolidation allows combining financial data from **multiple separate "
"companies**, each with its own books, into a unified view, providing a "
"\"fair image\" of the entire group's financial health."
msgstr ""
"Konsolidace umožňuje sloučit finanční data z **více samostatných "
"společností**, z nichž každá má vlastní účetnictví, do jednotného pohledu, "
"který poskytuje \"věrný obraz\" finančního zdraví celé skupiny."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:8
msgid ""
"It helps create a clear, comprehensive view of the group's financial "
"performance by combining data from multiple companies."
msgstr ""
"Pomáhá vytvořit jasný a komplexní pohled na finanční výkonnost skupiny "
"sloučením dat z více společností."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:12
msgid ""
"Consolidating companies involves **legally separate entities**, "
"whereas :ref:`branches <general/companies/branches>` are **subdivisions** of "
"a single legal entity which often share the head office's resources "
"(journals, taxes, accounts, fiscal positions) and are not consolidated in "
"the same way."
msgstr ""
"Konsolidering af virksomheder involverer **juridisk separate enheder**, "
"hvorimod :ref:`filialer <general/companies/branches>` er **underafdelinger** "
"af en enkelt juridisk enhed, som ofte deler hovedkontorets ressourcer "
"(journaler, skatter, konti, skattepositioner) og ikke konsolideres på samme "
"måde."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:20
msgid "Consolidation tools"
msgstr "Nástroje konsolidace"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:22
msgid ""
"**Several tools** combined together will contribute to the construction of "
"the financial consolidation:"
msgstr ""
"**Několik nástrojů** společně přispívá k vytvoření finanční konsolidace:"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:27
msgid ""
"**Account Mapping:** Similar accounts from different companies can be mapped "
"together. This allows Odoo to combine them correctly in consolidated "
"reports. To map accounts, go to :menuselection:`Accounting --> Configuration "
"--> Chart of Accounts`.  Click :guilabel:`View` on the account line. In "
"the :guilabel:`Mapping` tab, enter a code in the corresponding "
"company :guilabel:`Code` column to map the account."
msgstr ""
"**Mapování účtů:** Podobné účty z různých společností lze vzájemně "
"namapovat. To umožňuje systému Odoo správně je sloučit v konsolidovaných "
"sestavách. Pro mapování účtů přejděte na :menuselection:`Regnskab --> "
"Konfigurace --> Kontoplaner`. Klikněte na :guilabel:`Zobrazit` na řádku "
"účtu. Na kartě :guilabel:`Mapování` zadejte kód do sloupce :guilabel:`Kód` "
"příslušné společnosti pro namapování účtu."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:None
msgid "Mapping different codes to different companies."
msgstr "Mapování různých kódů do různých společností."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:36
msgid ""
":ref:`Import mapping <consolidation_import_account_mapping>` or merge "
"existing accounts using the :ref:`merging tool <consolidation_merge_tool>` "
"can simplify the process."
msgstr ""
":ref:`Import mapování <consolidation_import_account_mapping>` nebo sloučení "
"existujících účtů pomocí :ref:`nástroje pro slučování "
"<consolidation_merge_tool>` může proces zjednodušit."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:39
msgid ""
"When multiple accounts from one company are mapped to a single account in "
"another, it is then possible to group the multiple accounts into a single "
"line in the other company's reporting by :ref:`grouping by <customize-"
"reports/lines-group-by>` the *account code* (`account_code`) rather than the "
"*account ID* (`account_id`)."
msgstr ""
"Když je více účtů z jedné společnosti namapováno na jediný účet v jiné "
"společnosti, je pak možné seskupit tyto účty do jednoho řádku v sestavách "
"druhé společnosti pomocí :ref:`seskupení podle <customize-reports/lines-"
"group-by>` *kódu účtu* (`account_code`) místo *ID účtu* (`account_id`)."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:45
msgid ""
"Some reports, such as the :ref:`profit and loss <accounting/reporting/profit-"
"and-loss>`, split the lines into different sections by account type. When "
"these reports are grouped by account code, the section splits are "
"maintained, but within each section, line grouping by account code is "
"respected."
msgstr ""
"Některé sestavy, jako například :ref:`výkaz zisku a ztráty <accounting/"
"reporting/profit-and-loss>`, rozdělují řádky do různých sekcí podle typu "
"účtu. Když jsou tyto sestavy seskupeny podle kódu účtu, rozdělení na sekce "
"je zachováno, ale v rámci každé sekce je respektováno seskupení řádků podle "
"kódu účtu."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:51
msgid ""
"Belgian Company is a parent company with a subsidiary, American Company. "
"American Company has five income accounts:"
msgstr ""
"Belgian Company je mateřská společnost s dceřinou společností American "
"Company. American Company má pět výnosových účtů:"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:54
msgid "400000 Product Sales - Domestic"
msgstr "400000 produktsalg - indenlandsk"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:55
msgid "400100 Product Sales - International"
msgstr "400100 produktsalg - internationalt"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:56
msgid "410000 Service Revenue - Consulting"
msgstr "410000 serviceomsætning - konsulentvirksomhed"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:57
msgid "420000 Subscription Revenue"
msgstr "420000 abonnementsomsætning"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:58
msgid "430000 Freight & Handling Revenue"
msgstr "430000 fragt- og håndteringsomsætning"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:60
msgid ""
"All five of the US income accounts correspond to one single income account "
"(700000 Income) in the Belgian Company."
msgstr ""
"Alle fem amerikanske indtægtskonti svarer til én enkelt indtægtskonto "
"(700000 indtægt) i det belgiske selskab."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:63
msgid ""
"For the Belgian Company's profit and loss report to show one line for all of "
"the American Company's combined income accounts related to the Belgian "
"Company's single income account, all five income accounts from the American "
"Company must be mapped to The Belgian Company's 700000 Income account, and "
"the report's lines must be :ref:`grouped by <customize-reports/lines-group-"
"by>` the account code."
msgstr ""
"For at det belgiske selskabs resultatopgørelse skal vise én linje for alle "
"det amerikanske selskabs kombinerede indtægtskonti relateret til det "
"belgiske selskabs enkelte indtægtskonto, skal alle fem indtægtskonti fra det "
"amerikanske selskab knyttes til det belgiske selskabs 700000 indtægtskonto, "
"og rapportens linjer skal være :ref:`grupperet efter <customize-reports/"
"lines-group-by>` kontokoden."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:71
msgid ""
"**Multi-Ledgers:** Ledgers are fundamental to the process of consolidation. "
"They are either:"
msgstr ""
"**Flere finanser:** Finanser er grundlæggende for konsolideringsprocessen. "
"De er enten:"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:73
msgid ""
"*Regular Ledgers:* Each company in the consolidation scope has its own "
"standard accounting ledger where all the regular day-to-day transactions are "
"recorded. It excludes the company's consolidation adjustment journals."
msgstr ""
"*Almindelige finanser:* Hvert selskab i konsolideringsområdet har sin egen "
"standardfinans, hvor alle de almindelige daglige transaktioner registreres. "
"Det udelukker selskabets konsolideringsjusteringskladder."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:77
msgid ""
"*Multi-Ledger for Consolidation:* The company doing the actual consolidation "
"also has a special multi-ledger. This one includes all the other companies' "
"consolidation adjustments journals (the ones excluded from their own "
"ledgers). This allows for viewing the total impact of all the adjustments."
msgstr ""
"*Flere finanser til konsolidering:* Det selskab, der udfører selve "
"konsolideringen, har også en særlig finans med flere finanser. Denne "
"inkluderer alle de andre selskabers konsolideringsjusteringskladder (dem, "
"der er udelukket fra deres egne finanser). Dette giver mulighed for at se "
"den samlede effekt af alle justeringerne."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:82
msgid ""
"To create a new ledger, go to :menuselection:`Accounting --> Configuration --"
"> Multi-Ledgers` and hit the :guilabel:`New` button. Enter a name, pick the "
"company the ledger is linked to and most importantly, determine which "
"journals are to be excluded from the ledger."
msgstr ""
"For at oprette en ny finans skal du gå til :menuselection:`Regnskab --> "
"Konfiguration --> Flere finanser` og klikke på knappen :guilabel:`Ny`. Angiv "
"et navn, vælg det selskab, som finansen er knyttet til, og bestem især, "
"hvilke kladder der skal udelukkes fra finansen."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:91
msgid ""
"**Multi-Company Selector:** The consolidated view can be accessed using the "
"multi-company"
msgstr ""
"**Flere selskabsvælger:** Den konsoliderede visning kan tilgås ved hjælp af "
"vælgeren til flere selskaber."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:89
msgid ""
"selector. Selecting the consolidating company as the current company and "
"making the other companies visible in the selector, all the journal items "
"are displayed from the consolidating company's perspective."
msgstr ""
"Når du vælger det konsoliderende selskab som det aktuelle selskab og gør de "
"andre selskaber synlige i vælgeren, vises alle kladdeposter fra det "
"konsoliderende selskabs perspektiv."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:None
msgid "Selecting the main company and activating others."
msgstr "Valg af hovedselskabet og aktivering af andre."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:111
msgid ""
"**Horizontal Groups:** Odoo's reporting tools allow for combining multi-"
"ledgers and using"
msgstr ""
"**Horisontale grupper:** Odoos rapporteringsværktøjer giver mulighed for at "
"kombinere flere finanser og bruge"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:99
msgid ""
"horizontal groups to view the consolidated Balance Sheet or P&L. They also "
"show how much each company contributes to the overall consolidated figures."
msgstr ""
"horisontale grupper til at se den konsoliderede statusopgørelse eller "
"resultatopgørelse. De viser også, hvor meget hvert selskab bidrager til de "
"samlede konsoliderede tal."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:102
msgid "Follow these steps to create an :guilabel:`Horizontal Group`:"
msgstr "Følg disse trin for at oprette en :guilabel:`horisontal gruppe`:"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:105
msgid ""
"Go to :menuselection:`Accounting --> Configuration --> Horizontal Groups` "
"and click :guilabel:`New`."
msgstr ""
"Gå til :menuselection:`Regnskab --> Konfiguration --> Horisontale grupper` "
"og klik på :guilabel:`Ny`."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:107
msgid ""
"Add a :guilabel:`Group Name` and select the :guilabel:`Reports` where the "
"horizontal group can be used."
msgstr ""
"Tilføj et :guilabel:`gruppenavn`, og vælg de :guilabel:`rapporter`, hvor den "
"horisontale gruppe kan bruges."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:109
msgid "In the :guilabel:`Field` column, click :guilabel:`Add a line`."
msgstr ""
"I kolonnen :guilabel:`felt` skal du klikke på :guilabel:`Tilføj en linje`."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:110
msgid ""
"In the :guilabel:`Create rules` window, add a :guilabel:`Field` and create a "
"new :guilabel:`Domain` rule if needed. Then, click :guilabel:`Save & Close`."
msgstr ""
"I vinduet :guilabel:`Opret regler` tilføjes et :guilabel:`Felt`, og der "
"oprettes en ny :guilabel:`Domæne`-regel, hvis det er nødvendigt. Klik "
"derefter på :guilabel:`Gem og luk`."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:None
msgid "Using horizontal groups to see each company's contribution."
msgstr "Brug af horisontale grupper til at se hver virksomheds bidrag."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:117
msgid ""
"When opened, financial reports usually default to a statutory view, using "
"the company's regular ledger (including its consolidation adjustment). To "
"see the full consolidation picture, **make sure to select the multi-ledger** "
"that includes all the consolidation adjustments."
msgstr ""
"Når de åbnes, vises finansielle rapporter som standard i en lovpligtig "
"visning ved hjælp af virksomhedens almindelige finans (inklusive dens "
"konsolideringsjustering). For at se det fulde konsolideringsbillede skal du "
"**sørge for at vælge multifinansen**, der inkluderer alle "
"konsolideringsjusteringer."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:123
msgid ""
"**Cumulative Translation Adjustments:** When consolidating companies with "
"different currencies, Odoo handles the translation."
msgstr ""
"**Kumulative oversættelsesjusteringer:** Når virksomheder med forskellige "
"valutaer konsolideres, håndterer Odoo oversættelsen."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:126
msgid "*Equity accounts:* Use the historical exchange rate."
msgstr "*Egenkapitalkonti:* Brug den historiske valutakurs."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:128
msgid "*Profit & Loss (P&L) accounts:* Use the average exchange rate."
msgstr "*Resultatopgørelseskonti (P&L):* Brug den gennemsnitlige valutakurs."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:130
msgid ""
"*Balance sheet accounts (excluding equity):* Use the closing exchange rate."
msgstr "*Balancekonti (ekskl. egenkapital):* Brug slutkursen."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:133
msgid "The rates used are those of the company currently selected."
msgstr "De anvendte kurser er dem for den aktuelt valgte virksomhed."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:138
msgid "Account merging"
msgstr "Kontosammenlægning"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:140
msgid ""
"Accounts can be merged to reduce the number of accounts and standardize them "
"across companies. This is optional; consolidation works without it."
msgstr ""
"Konti kan sammenlægges for at reducere antallet af konti og standardisere "
"dem på tværs af virksomheder. Dette er valgfrit; konsolidering fungerer uden "
"det."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:143
msgid ""
"To use the merge tool, select all the companies with an account that needs "
"to be merged in the company selector in the top right corner of the screen."
msgstr ""
"For at bruge sammenlægningsværktøjet vælges alle de virksomheder, der har en "
"konto, som skal sammenlægges, i virksomhedsvælgeren i øverste højre hjørne "
"af skærmen."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:None
msgid "Selecting all companies that have accounts to be merged."
msgstr "Valg af alle virksomheder, der har konti, som skal sammenlægges."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:149
msgid ""
"Then, go to :menuselection:`Accounting --> Configuration --> Chart of "
"Accounts` and select the accounts to merge. Click the :icon:`fa-"
"cog` :guilabel:`Actions` menu and select :guilabel:`Merge accounts`."
msgstr ""
"Gå derefter til :menuselection:`Regnskab --> Konfiguration --> Kontoplaner`, "
"og vælg de konti, der skal sammenlægges. Klik på menuen :icon:`fa-"
"cog` :guilabel:`Handlinger`, og vælg :guilabel:`Sammenlæg konti`."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:153
msgid ""
"In the :guilabel:`Merge accounts` window, enable the :guilabel:`Group by "
"name?` option if needed and click :guilabel:`Merge`."
msgstr ""
"I vinduet :guilabel:`Sammenlæg konti` aktiveres "
"indstillingen :guilabel:`Gruppér efter navn?`, hvis det er nødvendigt, og "
"klik på :guilabel:`Sammenlæg`."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:156
msgid ""
"The selected accounts are then merged into a single shared account, "
"accessible by all the chosen companies, just as if the account had been "
"directly created to be shared."
msgstr ""
"De valgte konti sammenlægges derefter til en enkelt delt konto, der er "
"tilgængelig for alle de valgte virksomheder, præcis som hvis kontoen var "
"blevet oprettet direkte til at være delt."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:162
msgid "Account unmerging"
msgstr "Opdeling af konti"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:164
msgid "Accounts can also be unmerged if needed."
msgstr "Konti kan også opdeles, hvis det er nødvendigt."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:168
msgid ""
"Note that unmerging accounts **will not unmerge the chatters** of the "
"accounts. Once merged, the changes' histories are permanently merged."
msgstr ""
"Bemærk, at opdeling af konti **ikke vil opdele chats** for kontiene. Når de "
"er sammenlagt, er ændringernes historikker permanent sammenlagt."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:171
msgid ""
"To unmerge accounts, select a company with a shared account in the company "
"selector at the top right corner of the screen. Then, go "
"to :menuselection:`Accounting --> Configuration --> Chart of Accounts` and "
"select the account to unmerge. Click the :icon:`fa-cog` :guilabel:`Actions` "
"menu and select :guilabel:`Unmerge accounts`."
msgstr ""
"For at opdele konti vælges en virksomhed med en delt konto i "
"virksomhedsvælgeren i øverste højre hjørne af skærmen. Gå derefter "
"til :menuselection:`Regnskab --> Konfiguration --> Kontoplaner`, og vælg den "
"konto, der skal opdeles. Klik på menuen :icon:`fa-"
"cog` :guilabel:`Handlinger`, og vælg :guilabel:`Opdel konti`."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:176
msgid ""
"An :guilabel:`Odoo Warning` confirmation pop-up window will appear, listing "
"how the accounts will be split."
msgstr ""
"Et bekræftelsesvindue :guilabel:`Odoo-advarsel` vises med en liste over, "
"hvordan kontierne vil blive opdelt."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:None
msgid ""
"Confirmation wizard for the Unmerge Tool of the shared accounts feature."
msgstr ""
"Bekræftelsesguide for opdelingsværktøjet for funktionen til delte konti."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:182
msgid ""
"Click :guilabel:`Unmerge`. A new account linked to each company will be "
"created for the previously shared account."
msgstr ""
"Klik på :guilabel:`Opdel`. En ny konto, der er knyttet til hver virksomhed, "
"oprettes for den tidligere delte konto."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:188
msgid "Import a mapping"
msgstr "Importér en tilknytning"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:190
msgid ""
"To **import an account mapping**, select all the related companies in the "
"company selector at the top right corner of the screen and go "
"to :menuselection:`Accounting --> Configuration --> Chart of Accounts`."
msgstr ""
"For at **importere en kontokobling** skal du vælge alle de relaterede "
"virksomheder i virksomhedsvælgeren øverst i højre hjørne af skærmen og gå "
"til :menuselection:`Regnskab --> Konfiguration --> Kontoplaner`."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:194
msgid ""
"First, to choose the fields to export, select the accounts, click "
"the :icon:`fa-cog` :guilabel:`Actions` button and select :guilabel:`Export`. "
"Then, in the :guilabel:`Export data` window, add the :guilabel:`Code mapping/"
"Code`, :guilabel:`Code Mapping/Company` and :guilabel:`External ID` fields "
"using the :icon:`fa-plus` icon and click :guilabel:`Export`. No other field "
"is required."
msgstr ""
"Først skal du vælge felterne til eksport ved at vælge konti, klikke "
"på :icon:`fa-cog` :guilabel:`Handlinger` knappen og "
"vælge :guilabel:`Eksporter`. Dernæst i :guilabel:`Eksporter data` vinduet "
"skal du tilføje felterne :guilabel:`Kodekobling/"
"Kode`, :guilabel:`Kodekobling/Virksomhed` og :guilabel:`Eksternt ID` ved "
"hjælp af :icon:`fa-plus` ikonet og klikke på :guilabel:`Eksporter`. Ingen "
"andre felter er påkrævet."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:200
msgid ""
"Second, rework it in a spreadsheet adding the desired code for each company "
"on desired accounts."
msgstr ""
"Dernæst skal du omarbejde den i et regneark og tilføje den ønskede kode for "
"hver virksomhed på de ønskede konti."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:202
msgid ""
"Third, to reimport the file (xlsx or csv format) in Odoo, "
"click :guilabel:`Import` and, in the :guilabel:`Import Chart of Accounts` "
"section, click :guilabel:`Import CoA`. In the :guilabel:`Accounting Import "
"Guide`, drop or click :guilabel:`Upload Data File` to import the file. Then, "
"click :guilabel:`Import`."
msgstr ""
"Til sidst skal du genimportere filen (xlsx eller csv format) i Odoo ved at "
"klikke på :guilabel:`Importer` og i afsnittet :guilabel:`Importer kontoplan` "
"klikke på :guilabel:`Importer kontoplan`. I :guilabel:`Regnskab Importguide` "
"skal du slippe eller klikke på :guilabel:`Upload datafil` for at importere "
"filen. Klik derefter på :guilabel:`Importer`."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/consolidation.rst:207
msgid ""
"Finally, the codes now take into account the mapping company per company."
msgstr ""
"Endelig tager koderne nu højde for koblingen virksomhed for virksomhed."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:3
#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/multi_currency.rst:99
#: ../../content/applications/finance/fiscal_localizations/argentina.rst:260
#: ../../content/applications/finance/fiscal_localizations/chile.rst:283
#: ../../content/applications/finance/fiscal_localizations/france.rst:637
#: ../../content/applications/finance/fiscal_localizations/india.rst:126
#: ../../content/applications/finance/fiscal_localizations/peru.rst:365
msgid "Journals"
msgstr "Journaler"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:5
msgid ""
"Journal entries are recorded in different **journals** to maintain an "
"organized record of a company's financial transactions. Odoo uses six "
"different types of journals to organize accounting records:"
msgstr ""
"Poster registreres i forskellige **kladder** for at opretholde en "
"organiseret registrering af en virksomheds finansielle transaktioner. Odoo "
"bruger seks forskellige typer kladder til at organisere regnskabsposter:"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:9
msgid ":ref:`Bank <accounting/journals/bank>`"
msgstr ":ref:`Bank <accounting/journals/bank>`"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:10
msgid ":ref:`Cash <accounting/journals/cash>`"
msgstr ":ref:`Kontant <accounting/journals/cash>`"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:11
msgid ":ref:`Credit Card <accounting/journals/credit>`"
msgstr ":ref:`Kreditkort <accounting/journals/credit>`"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:12
msgid ":ref:`Sales <accounting/journals/sales>`"
msgstr ":ref:`Salg <accounting/journals/sales>`"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:13
msgid ":ref:`Purchase <accounting/journals/purchase>`"
msgstr ":ref:`Indkøb <accounting/journals/purchase>`"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:14
msgid ":ref:`Miscellaneous <accounting/journals/misc>`"
msgstr ":ref:`Diverse <accounting/journals/misc>`"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:17
msgid ""
"It is possible to have multiple journals of the same type, such as two "
"separate bank journals, each for a unique bank account, or two separate "
"sales journals to track :abbr:`B2B (business to business)` versus :abbr:`B2C "
"(business to customer)` income."
msgstr ""
"Det er muligt at have flere kladder af samme type, såsom to separate "
"bankkladder, hver for en unik bankkonto, eller to separate salgskladder til "
"at spore :abbr:`B2B (business to business)` versus :abbr:`B2C (business to "
"customer)` indkomst."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:21
msgid ""
"Each card on the :guilabel:`Accounting Dashboard` represents a journal. To "
"edit the configuration of a journal, click the :icon:`fa-ellipsis-"
"v` :guilabel:`(vertical ellipsis)` on the journal card, then "
"click :guilabel:`Configuration`. Alternatively, go "
"to :menuselection:`Accounting --> Configuration --> Journals` to select and "
"edit an existing journal or to create a new one."
msgstr ""
"Hvert kort på :guilabel:`Regnskab Dashboard` repræsenterer en kladde. For at "
"redigere konfigurationen af en kladde skal du klikke på :icon:`fa-ellipsis-"
"v` :guilabel:`(lodret ellipse)` på kladdekort, derefter klikke "
"på :guilabel:`Konfiguration`. Alternativt kan du gå "
"til :menuselection:`Regnskab --> Konfiguration --> Kladder` for at vælge og "
"redigere en eksisterende kladde eller oprette en ny."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:26
msgid ""
"While different journal types have slightly different fields to configure, "
"some fields are consistent across all the journal types:"
msgstr ""
"Mens forskellige kladdetyper har lidt forskellige felter at konfigurere, er "
"nogle felter ensartede på tværs af alle kladdetyper:"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:29
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Short Code`: Each journal must have a unique code (from 1 to 5 "
"characters long). The short code is used as the prefix for all journal "
"entries belonging to this journal."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Kort kode`: Hver kladde skal have en unik kode (fra 1 til 5 tegn "
"lang). Den korte kode bruges som præfiks for alle poster, der tilhører denne "
"kladde."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:31
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Currency`: If desired, set the currency of this journal. For bank "
"and cash journals, this is the currency of the journal's :doc:`transactions "
"<../bank/transactions>`. This field is only visible when :doc:`multiple "
"currencies <multi_currency>` are enabled."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Valuta`: Hvis ønsket, indstil valutaen for denne kladde. For "
"bank- og kontantkladder er dette valutaen for kladdenes :doc:`transaktioner "
"<../bank/transactions>`. Dette felt er kun synligt, når :doc:`flere valutaer "
"<multi_currency>` er aktiveret."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:35
msgid "The :guilabel:`Advanced Settings` tab contains more technical options:"
msgstr ""
"Fanen :guilabel:`Avancerede indstillinger` indeholder mere tekniske "
"indstillinger:"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:37
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Allowed accounts`: Limit which accounts are available when "
"recording journal entries in this journal. Leave this field blank to allow "
"all accounts."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Tilladte konti`: Begræns hvilke konti der er tilgængelige ved "
"registrering af posteringer i denne journal. Lad dette felt være tomt for at "
"tillade alle konti."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:39
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Email Alias`: Set an email address to create journal entries by "
"digitizing PDFs sent to this address. This is most commonly used to "
"create :ref:`customer invoices and vendor bills <accounting/bill-"
"digitization/email-alias>`."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`E-mail-alias`: Angiv en e-mail-adresse for at oprette posteringer "
"ved at digitalisere PDF'er sendt til denne adresse. Dette bruges oftest til "
"at oprette :ref:`kundefakturaer og leverandørfakturaer <accounting/bill-"
"digitization/email-alias>`."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:42
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Secure Posted Entries with Hash`: Restrict the :doc:`alterability "
"<../reporting/data_inalterability>` of this journal's entries to comply with "
"tax authorities in certain countries."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Sikre bogførte posteringer med hash`: Begræns :doc:`ænderbarheden "
"<../reporting/data_inalterability>` af denne journals posteringer for at "
"overholde skattemyndighedernes krav i visse lande."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:47
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Secure Posted Entries with Hash` option cannot be removed "
"from a journal once the journal has a posted journal entry."
msgstr ""
"Indstillingen :guilabel:`Sikre bogførte posteringer med hash` kan ikke "
"fjernes fra en journal, når journalen har en bogført postering."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:51
msgid ""
"Bank and cash journals do not have the :guilabel:`Secure Posted Entries with "
"Hash` or :guilabel:`Email Alias` fields."
msgstr ""
"Bank- og kontantjournaler har ikke felterne :guilabel:`Sikre bogførte "
"posteringer med hash` eller :guilabel:`E-mail-alias`."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:53
msgid ""
"If an :ref:`alias domain <email-inbound-custom-domain>` has not yet been "
"configured, a link to :icon:`fa-arrow-right` :guilabel:`Configure Alias "
"Domain` is displayed instead of the :guilabel:`Email Alias` field."
msgstr ""
"Hvis et :ref:`aliasdomæne <email-inbound-custom-domain>` endnu ikke er "
"konfigureret, vises et link til :icon:`fa-arrow-right` :guilabel:`Konfigurer "
"aliasdomæne` i stedet for feltet :guilabel:`E-mail-alias`."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:60
msgid "Bank, cash, and credit card journals"
msgstr "Bank-, kontant- og kreditkortjournaler"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:62
msgid "Bank, cash, and credit card journals share the following features:"
msgstr "Bank-, kontant- og kreditkortjournaler deler følgende funktioner:"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:64
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Suspense Account`: :doc:`../bank/transactions` on this journal "
"are posted on this account until they are reconciled, at which point this "
"account is replaced with the account the transaction was reconciled against. "
"At any moment, the suspense account's balance in the general ledger shows "
"the balance of transactions that have not yet been reconciled."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Suspensekonto`: :doc:`../bank/transactions` i denne journal "
"bogføres på denne konto, indtil de afstemmes, hvorefter denne konto "
"erstattes med den konto, transaktionen blev afstemt med. På ethvert "
"tidspunkt viser suspensekontoens saldo i hovedbogen saldoen for "
"transaktioner, der endnu ikke er afstemt."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:70
msgid ""
"When a bank transaction is reconciled, the journal entry is modified to "
"replace the bank suspense account with the account of the journal item it is "
"reconciled with. This account is usually either:"
msgstr ""
"Når en banktransaktion afstemmes, ændres posteringen for at erstatte "
"banksuspensekontoen med kontoen for den journalpost, den afstemmes med. "
"Denne konto er normalt enten:"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:74
msgid ""
"the :ref:`outstanding receipts or payments account <accounting/journals/"
"outstanding-accounts>` if reconciling with a registered payment; or"
msgstr ""
":ref:`kontoen for udestående indbetalinger eller betalinger <accounting/"
"journals/outstanding-accounts>`, hvis den afstemmes med en registreret "
"betaling; eller"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:76
msgid ""
"the account receivable or payable if reconciling with an invoice or bill "
"directly."
msgstr ""
"debitor- eller kreditorkontoen, hvis den afstemmes direkte med en faktura "
"eller leverandørfaktura."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:78
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Dedicated Payment Sequence`: Tick this field to use separate "
"sequences for payments and transactions posted on this journal."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Dedikeret betalingssekvens`: Marker dette felt for at bruge "
"separate sekvenser til betalinger og transaktioner bogført i denne journal."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:82
msgid ""
"If the :guilabel:`Dedicated Payment Sequence` field is ticked, payments that "
"use an :ref:`outstanding account <accounting/journals/outstanding-accounts>` "
"will have references that add :guilabel:`P` before the journal's short code. "
"Otherwise, the references will begin with :guilabel:`PAY`."
msgstr ""
"Hvis feltet :guilabel:`Dedikeret betalingssekvens` er markeret, vil "
"betalinger der bruger en :ref:`udestående konto <accounting/journals/"
"outstanding-accounts>`, have referencer der tilføjer :guilabel:`P` før "
"journalens korte kode. Ellers vil referencerne begynde med :guilabel:`PAY`."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:87
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Incoming Payments` and :guilabel:`Outgoing Payments` tabs "
"contain the :ref:`payment methods <accounting/payments/payment-methods>` of "
"this journal. Different payment methods are available depending on the "
"journal type. If desired, set :ref:`outstanding accounts <accounting/"
"journals/outstanding-accounts>` on the payment methods."
msgstr ""
"Fanerne :guilabel:`Indgående betalinger` og :guilabel:`Udgående betalinger` "
"indeholder denne journals :ref:`betalingsmetoder <accounting/payments/"
"payment-methods>`. Forskellige betalingsmetoder er tilgængelige afhængigt af "
"journaltypen. Angiv om ønsket :ref:`udestående konti <accounting/journals/"
"outstanding-accounts>` på betalingsmetoderne."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:94
msgid ":doc:`multi_currency`"
msgstr ":doc:`multi_currency`"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:95
msgid ":doc:`../bank/transactions`"
msgstr ":doc:`../bank/transactions`"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:96
msgid "`Bank configuration <https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tVhhXw-VnGE>`_"
msgstr "`Bankkonfiguration <https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tVhhXw-VnGE>`_"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:101
msgid "Outstanding accounts"
msgstr "Udestående konti"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:103
msgid ""
"By default, payments in Odoo do not create journal entries, but they can be "
"configured to create journal entries by using **outstanding accounts** "
"on :ref:`bank <accounting/journals/bank>` and :ref:`cash <accounting/"
"journals/cash>` journals."
msgstr ""
"Som standard opretter betalinger i Odoo ikke posteringer, men de kan "
"konfigureres til at oprette posteringer ved at bruge **udestående konti** "
"på :ref:`bank- <accounting/journals/bank>` og :ref:`kontant <accounting/"
"journals/cash>`journaler."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:107
msgid ""
"An **outstanding receipts account** is where incoming payments are posted "
"until they are linked with incoming bank transactions."
msgstr ""
"En **udestående indbetalingskonto** er, hvor indgående betalinger bogføres, "
"indtil de kædes sammen med indgående banktransaktioner."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:109
msgid ""
"An **outstanding payments account** is where outgoing payments are posted "
"until they are linked with outgoing bank transactions."
msgstr ""
"En **udestående udbetalingskonto** er, hvor udgående betalinger bogføres, "
"indtil de kædes sammen med udgående banktransaktioner."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:112
msgid ""
"These accounts are usually of :ref:`type <chart-of-account/"
"type>` :guilabel:`Current Assets` and :guilabel:`Current Liabilities`."
msgstr ""
"Disse konti er normalt af :ref:`type <chart-of-account/"
"type>` :guilabel:`Omsætningsaktiver` og :guilabel:`Kortfristet gæld`."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:115
msgid ""
"Payments that are registered in Odoo are posted to the outstanding receipts "
"and outstanding payments accounts until they are reconciled. At any moment, "
"the outstanding receipts account's balance in the general ledger shows the "
"balance of registered incoming payments that have not yet been reconciled, "
"and the outstanding payments account's balance in the general ledger shows "
"the balance of registered outgoing payments that have not yet been "
"reconciled."
msgstr ""
"Betalinger der registreres i Odoo, bogføres på kontiene for udestående "
"indbetalinger og udestående betalinger, indtil de afstemmes. På ethvert "
"tidspunkt viser kontoen for udestående indbetalingers saldo i hovedbogen "
"saldoen for registrerede indgående betalinger, der endnu ikke er afstemt, og "
"kontoen for udestående betalingers saldo i hovedbogen viser saldoen for "
"registrerede udgående betalinger, der endnu ikke er afstemt."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:124
msgid ""
"To configure outstanding accounts, go to :menuselection:`Accounting --> "
"Configuration --> Journals` and select or create a bank or cash journal. In "
"the :guilabel:`Incoming Payments` and :guilabel:`Outgoing Payments` tabs, "
"set :guilabel:`Outstanding Receipts accounts` and :guilabel:`Outstanding "
"Payments accounts` for each payment method that you want to create journal "
"entries."
msgstr ""
"For at konfigurere udestående konti skal du gå til :menuselection:`Regnskab "
"--> Konfiguration --> Journaler` og vælge eller oprette en bank- eller "
"kontantjournal. I fanerne :guilabel:`Indgående betalinger` "
"og :guilabel:`Udgående betalinger` skal du angive :guilabel:`Konti for "
"udestående indbetalinger` og :guilabel:`Konti for udestående betalinger` for "
"hver betalingsmetode, hvor du ønsker at oprette posteringer."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:131
msgid ""
"If the main bank account of the journal is added as an outstanding receipts "
"account or outstanding payments account, when a payment is registered, the "
"invoice or bill's status is directly set to :guilabel:`Paid`."
msgstr ""
"Hvis hovedbankkontoen for kladden tilføjes som en udestående "
"indbetalingskonto eller udestående udbetalingskonto, indstilles fakturaens "
"eller regningens status direkte til :guilabel:`Betalt`, når en betaling "
"registreres."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:134
msgid ""
"If the outstanding receipts or outstanding payments account for a payment "
"method is left blank, registering a payment with that payment method will "
"not create any journal entry."
msgstr ""
"Hvis kontoen for udestående kvitteringer eller udestående betalinger for en "
"betalingsmetode er tom, vil registrering af en betaling med denne "
"betalingsmetode ikke oprette nogen journalpost."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:142
msgid ""
"Bank journals are used to record journal entries related to :doc:`bank "
"transactions <../bank/transactions>` and incoming and "
"outgoing :doc:`payments <../payments>`. The following fields are specific to "
"bank journals:"
msgstr ""
"Bankkladder bruges til at registrere kladdeposteringer relateret "
"til :doc:`banktransaktioner <../bank/transactions>` og indgående og "
"udgående :doc:`betalinger <../payments>`. Følgende felter er specifikke for "
"bankkladder:"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:146
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Bank Account`: This :guilabel:`Bank and Cash` type account is the "
"default account for this bank journal."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Bankkonto`: Denne konto af typen :guilabel:`Bank og kontant` er "
"standardkontoen for denne bankkladde."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:148
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Account Number`: The bank account's number is used when "
"registering payments and is required for generating outgoing payment files, "
"such as :doc:`SEPA <../payments/sepa_payments>` or :ref:`NACHA <l10n_us/"
"nacha>`. To edit the bank account details, click on the :icon:`oi-arrow-"
"right` :guilabel:`(Internal link)` button next to the :guilabel:`Account "
"Number` and update the account information accordingly."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Kontonummer`: Bankkontoens nummer bruges ved registrering af "
"betalinger og er påkrævet for generering af udgående betalingsfiler, såsom "
":doc:`SEPA <../payments/sepa_payments>` eller :ref:`NACHA <l10n_us/nacha>`. "
"For at redigere bankkontooplysningerne skal du klikke på knappen :icon:`oi-"
"arrow-right` :guilabel:`(Internt link)` ved siden af :guilabel:`Kontonummer` "
"og opdatere kontooplysningerne i overensstemmelse hermed."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:153
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Bank`: The bank name is used when registering payments and is "
"required for generating outgoing payment files. To edit the bank account "
"details, click on the :icon:`oi-arrow-right` :guilabel:`(Internal link)` "
"button next to the :guilabel:`Bank` name and update the account information "
"accordingly."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Bank`: Banknavnet bruges ved registrering af betalinger og er "
"påkrævet for at generere udgående betalingsfiler. For at redigere "
"bankkontooplysningerne skal du klikke på knappen :icon:`oi-arrow-"
"right` :guilabel:`(Internt link)` ved siden af :guilabel:`Bank`-navnet og "
"opdatere kontooplysningerne i overensstemmelse hermed."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:157
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Bank Feeds`: Define the method of creating "
"bank :doc:`transactions <../bank/transactions>`, whether :guilabel:`Manual` "
"or via :doc:`Online Synchronization <../bank/bank_synchronization>`."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Bankfeeds`: Definer metoden til oprettelse af "
"bank-:doc:`transaktioner <../bank/transactions>`, enten :guilabel:`Manuel` "
"eller via :doc:`Onlinesynkronisering <../bank/bank_synchronization>`."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:160
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Split Transactions`: Split collective payments for CODA files."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Opdel transaktioner`: Opdel kollektive betalinger for CODA-filer."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:162
msgid ""
"Multiple payment methods are available for bank journals, as are "
"configurations for generating outgoing payment files, such as :doc:`SEPA <../"
"payments/sepa_payments>` or :ref:`NACHA <l10n_us/nacha>`."
msgstr ""
"Flere betalingsmetoder er tilgængelige for bankjournaler, ligesom "
"konfigurationer til generering af udgående betalingsfiler, såsom :doc:`SEPA "
"<../payments/sepa_payments>` eller :ref:`NACHA <l10n_us/nacha>`."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:169
#: ../../content/applications/finance/fiscal_localizations/united_arab_emirates.rst:74
msgid "Cash"
msgstr "Kontant"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:171
msgid ""
"Cash journals are used to record journal entries related to "
"cash :doc:`transactions <../bank/transactions>`. The following fields are "
"specific to cash journals:"
msgstr ""
"Kontantkladder bruges til at registrere kladdeposteringer relateret til "
"kontant-:doc:`transaktioner <../bank/transactions>`. Følgende felter er "
"specifikke for kontantkladder:"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:174
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Cash Account`: This :guilabel:`Bank and Cash` type account is the "
"default account for this cash journal."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Kontantkonto`: Denne konto af typen :guilabel:`Bank og kontant` "
"er standardkontoen for denne kontantkladde."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:176
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Profit Account`: This :guilabel:`Income` or :guilabel:`Other "
"Income` type account is used to register a profit when the ending balance of "
"a cash register is greater than expected."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Overskudskonto`: Denne konto af typen :guilabel:`Indtægt` "
"eller :guilabel:`Anden indtægt` bruges til at registrere et overskud, når "
"slutsaldoen i et kasseapparat er større end forventet."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:178
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Loss Account`: This :guilabel:`Expenses` type account is used to "
"register a loss when the ending balance of a cash register is less than "
"expected."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Tabskonto`: Denne konto af typen :guilabel:`Øvrige omkostninger` "
"bruges til at registrere et tab, når slutsaldoen i et kasseapparat er mindre "
"end forventet."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:181
msgid "Only manual payment methods are available for cash journals."
msgstr "Kun manuelle betalingsmetoder er tilgængelige for kontantkladder."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:186
msgid "Credit card"
msgstr "Kreditkort"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:188
msgid ""
"Credit card journals are used to record journal entries related to credit "
"cards. The following fields are specific to credit card journals:"
msgstr ""
"Kreditkortkladder bruges til at registrere kladdeposteringer relateret til "
"kreditkort. Følgende felter er specifikke for kreditkortkladder:"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:191
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Journal Account`: This :guilabel:`Credit Card` type account is "
"the default account for this credit card journal."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Kladdekonto`: Denne konto af typen :guilabel:`Kreditkort` er "
"standardkontoen for denne kreditkortkladde."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:193
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Bank Feeds`: Define the method of creating credit card "
"transactions, whether manual or via :doc:`Online Synchronization <../bank/"
"bank_synchronization>`."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Bankfeeds`: Definer metoden til oprettelse af "
"kreditorkorttransaktioner, enten manuel eller via :doc:`Onlinesynkronisering "
"<../bank/bank_synchronization>`."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:196
msgid "Only manual payment methods are available for credit card journals."
msgstr "Kun manuelle betalingsmetoder er tilgængelige for kreditkortkladder."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:201
msgid "Sales, purchase, and miscellaneous journals"
msgstr "Salgs-, indkøbs- og diverse kladder"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:208
msgid ""
"Sales journals, also known as income journals, are used to record journal "
"entries related to :doc:`customer invoices <../customer_invoices>`. The "
"following fields are specific to customer invoice journals:"
msgstr ""
"Salgskladder, også kendt som indtægtskladder, bruges til at registrere "
"kladdeposteringer relateret til :doc:`kundefakturaer <../"
"customer_invoices>`. Følgende felter er specifikke for kundefakturakladder:"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:212
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Default Income Account`: Invoices in this journal use "
"this :guilabel:`Income` or :guilabel:`Other Income` type account unless "
"overwritten by another income account set on the product category, product, "
"or invoice line itself."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Standardindtægtskonto`: Fakturaer i denne kladde bruger denne "
"konto af typen :guilabel:`Indtægt` eller :guilabel:`Anden indtægt`, "
"medmindre den overskrives af en anden indtægtskonto, der er angivet på "
"produktkategorien, produktet eller selve fakturalinjen."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:215
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Dedicated Credit Note Sequence`: Check this box to use a separate "
"sequence for the reference of credit notes that increments separately from "
"the main invoice sequence and adds an `R` to the reference before the "
"journal's short code."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Dedikeret kreditnotasekvens`: Marker dette felt for at bruge en "
"separat sekvens til referencen for kreditnotaer, der øges separat fra "
"hovedfakturasekvensen og tilføjer et `R` til referencen før kladdens korte "
"kode."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:218
#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:247
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Dedicated Debit Note Sequence`: Check this box to use a separate "
"sequence for the reference of credit notes that increments separately from "
"the main invoice sequence and adds a `D` before the journal's short code."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Dedikeret debetnotasekvens`: Marker dette felt for at bruge en "
"separat sekvens til referencen for kreditnotaer, der øges uafhængigt af "
"hovedfakturasekvensen og tilføjer et `D` før journalens korte kode."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:222
msgid ""
"Sales journals have additional fields in the :guilabel:`Advanced Settings` "
"tab that allow you to set the default communication format that will appear "
"on customer invoices so that the customer can refer to that particular "
"invoice when making a payment:"
msgstr ""
"Salgsjournaler har yderligere felter i fanen :guilabel:`Avancerede "
"indstillinger`, som gør det muligt at indstille det "
"standardkommunikationsformat, der vises på kundefakturaer, så kunden kan "
"henvise til den pågældende faktura ved betaling:"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:226
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Communication Type`: Choose if the format of the payment "
"reference communicated to the customer should be based on the invoice number "
"or the customer's number."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Kommunikationstype`: Vælg om formatet for betalingsreferencen, "
"der kommunikeres til kunden, skal baseres på fakturanummeret eller kundens "
"nummer."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:228
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Communication Standard`: Choose the format of the payment "
"reference itself that is communicated to the customer."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Kommunikationsstandard`: Vælg formatet for selve "
"betalingsreferencen, der kommunikeres til kunden."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:234
msgid "Purchase"
msgstr "Indkøb"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:236
msgid ""
"Purchase journals are used to record journal entries related to :doc:`vendor "
"bills <../vendor_bills>`. The following fields are specific to purchase "
"journals:"
msgstr ""
"Indkøbsjournaler bruges til at registrere journalposteringer relateret "
"til :doc:`leverandørfakturaer <../vendor_bills>`. Følgende felter er "
"specifikke for indkøbsjournaler:"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:239
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Default Expense Account`: Vendor bills in this journal use "
"this :guilabel:`Expense` type account unless overwritten by another expense "
"account set on the product category, product, or expense."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Standardomkostningskonto`: Leverandørfakturaer i denne journal "
"bruger denne :guilabel:`Øvrige omkostninger`-typekonto, medmindre den "
"overskrives af en anden omkostningskonto angivet på produktkategorien, "
"produktet eller omkostningen."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:242
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Private Part Account`: Select the account to be used to register "
"the private part of mixed expenses."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Privat delkonto`: Vælg den konto, der skal bruges til at "
"registrere den private del af blandede omkostninger."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:244
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Dedicated Credit Note Sequence`: Check this box to use a separate "
"sequence for the reference of credit notes that increments separately from "
"the main vendor bill sequence and adds an `R` to the reference before the "
"journal's short code."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Dedikeret kreditnotasekvens`: Marker dette felt for at bruge en "
"separat sekvens til referencen for kreditnotaer, der øges uafhængigt af "
"hovedleverandørfakturasekvensen og tilføjer et `R` til referencen før "
"journalens korte kode."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:254
msgid "Miscellaneous"
msgstr "Diverse"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:256
msgid ""
"Miscellaneous journals are used to record journal entries that are not "
"related to any of the other journal types such as tax closing journal "
"entries."
msgstr ""
"Diverse journaler bruges til at registrere journalposteringer, der ikke er "
"relateret til nogen af de andre journaltyper, såsom "
"skatteafslutningsjournalposteringer."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/get_started/journals.rst:260
msgid ""
"`Tax return eLearning <https://www.odoo.com/slides/slide/tax-return-10564>`_"
msgstr ""
"`Selvangivelse eLearning <https://www.odoo.com/slides/slide/tax-"
"return-10564>`_"

