"The pay pop-up window filled out for multiple reimbursements via checks."
msgstr "Pop op-vinduet til betaling udfyldt for flere godtgørelser via checks."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/expenses/reinvoice_expenses.rst:3
msgid "Re-invoice expenses"
msgstr "Refakturer udgifter"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/expenses/reinvoice_expenses.rst:5
msgid ""
"If expenses are tracked on customer projects, they can be automatically "
"charged back to the customer. This is done by :ref:`creating an expense "
"<expenses/reinvoice-create>`, referencing the sales order to which it is "
"added, then :ref:`creating an expense report <expenses/reinvoice-report>`."
msgstr ""
"Hvis udgifter spores på kundeprojekter, kan de automatisk faktureres til "
"kunden. Dette gøres ved at :ref:`oprette en udgift <expenses/reinvoice-"
"create>`, med reference til den salgsordre, den føjes til, og derefter "
":ref:`oprette en udgiftsrapport <expenses/reinvoice-report>`."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/expenses/reinvoice_expenses.rst:10
msgid ""
"Next, managers :ref:`approve the expense report <expenses/reinvoice-"
"approve>`, before the accounting department :ref:`posts the journal entries "
"<expenses/reinvoice-approve>`."
msgstr ""
"Derefter :ref:`godkender ledere udgiftsrapporten <expenses/reinvoice-approve>"
"`, før bogføringsafdelingen :ref:`bogfører posteringerne <expenses/reinvoice-"
"approve>`."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/expenses/reinvoice_expenses.rst:13
msgid ""
"Finally, once the expense report is posted to a journal, the expenses appear "
"on the specified :abbr:`SO (Sales Order)`. The :abbr:`SO (Sales Order)` is "
"then :ref:`invoiced <expenses/reinvoice>`, thus charging the customer for "
"the expenses."
msgstr ""
"Når udgiftsrapporten endelig er bogført i en kladde, vises udgifterne på den "
"angivne :abbr:`SO (salgsordre)`. :abbr:`SO'en (salgsordre)` :ref:`faktureres "
"<expenses/reinvoice>` derefter, og kunden opkræves således for udgifterne."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/expenses/reinvoice_expenses.rst:18
msgid ""
"The **Sales** and **Accounting** apps must be installed for this "
"configuration."
msgstr ""
"Appene **Salg** og **Bogføring** skal være installeret for denne "
"konfiguration."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/expenses/reinvoice_expenses.rst:20
msgid ""
"Approving expenses, posting expenses to accounting, and re-invoicing "
"expenses on :abbr:`SOs (Sales Orders)` are **only** possible for users with "
"the appropriate :doc:`access rights <../../general/users/access_rights>`."
msgstr ""
"Godkendelse af udgifter, bogføring af udgifter og refakturering af udgifter "
"på :abbr:`SO'er (salgsordrer)` er **kun** mulig for brugere med de relevante "
":doc:`adgangsrettigheder <../../general/users/access_rights>`."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/expenses/reinvoice_expenses.rst:25
msgid ""
"This document provides lower-level instructions to create, submit, approve, "
"and post expenses. For fully-detailed instructions for any of these steps, "
"refer to the following documentation:"
msgstr ""
"Dette dokument indeholder instruktioner på lavere niveau til at oprette, "
"indsende, godkende og bogføre udgifter. For fuldstændige instruktioner til "
"disse trin henvises til følgende dokumentation:"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/expenses/reinvoice_expenses.rst:28
msgid ":doc:`Log expenses <log_expenses>`"
msgstr ":doc:`Registrer udgifter <log_expenses>`"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/expenses/reinvoice_expenses.rst:29
msgid ":doc:`Expense reports <expense_reports>`"
msgstr ":doc:`Udgiftsrapporter <expense_reports>`"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/expenses/reinvoice_expenses.rst:30
msgid ":doc:`Approving expenses <approve_expenses>`"
msgstr ":doc:`Godkendelse af udgifter <approve_expenses>`"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/expenses/reinvoice_expenses.rst:31
msgid ":doc:`Posting expenses in accounting <post_expenses>`"
msgstr ":doc:`Bogføring af udgifter <post_expenses>`"

